# Project Rules

Replace this file with rules specific to your project. Examples of what belongs here:

- What the project *is* — a one-line description of the user-visible product.
- Stack constraints — language, runtime, framework, package manager, target platforms.
- Non-negotiable product rules — accessibility floors, supported browsers, offline behavior, mobile-first requirements.
- External integrations the project must respect — APIs, data sources, deployment targets.
- Anything domain-specific that engineering and workflow rules should defer to.

Keep this file short. If a rule applies to every project the team runs, it belongs in `engineering.prompt` or `workflow.prompt` instead.
